Interface MembershipOracle<I,O>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Filter<I,O>, MembershipOracle.DFAMembershipOracle<I>, MembershipOracle.MealyMembershipOracle<I,O>, StatisticOracle<I,O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSingleQueryOracle, CounterOracle, CounterOracle.DFACounterOracle, CounterOracle.MealyCounterOracle, DFACacheOracle, FilterChain, HistogramOracle, MealyCacheOracle, ParallelOracle, QueryAnswererOracle, SafeOracle, SimulatorOracle, SimulatorOracle.DFASimulatorOracle, SimulatorOracle.MealySimulatorOracle, SULOracle

    public interface MembershipOracle<I,O>
    Membership oracle interface. A membership oracle provides an elementary abstraction to a System Under Learning (SUL), by allowing to pose DefaultQuerys: A query is a sequence of input symbols (divided into a prefix and a suffix part, cf. AbstractQuery.getPrefix() and AbstractQuery.getSuffix(), in reaction to which the SUL produces a specific observable behavior (outputting a word, acceptance/rejection etc.).
    Author:
    Malte Isberner , Maik Merten
    See Also:
    DefaultQuery

        void processQueries(Collection<? extends Query<I,O>> queries)
        Processes the specified collection of queries. When this method returns, the output field of each of the contained queries should reflect the SUL response to the respective query.
        Parameters:
        queries - the queries to process
